Logic Assignment - Imagine you are testing a web application for an online store. When a new user registers, the system displays a message confirming successful registration and sends an email to the email address provided during registration. You have noticed that sometimes users who have successfully registered do not receive the confirmation email. How would you investigate this issue?
Write a plan to investigate the email problem, identify the cause of the malfunction, and make appropriate recommendations to improve the application's performance. Include steps from hypothesis formulation to testing the results in your plan.


My plan to investigate the email problem

Possible causes of the problem:

Email is not sent due to an error in the backend
Email is sent with a delay
Email goes to the "Spam" folder
Incorrect email address validation
Problems with the email service
An error during loading
Email is not sent in all cases

Reproducing the problem

Perform a series of registrations with different email addresses (different domains: gmail, ukr.net, outlook, etc.)
Use different browsers and devices
Record the results (email received or not)
Determine whether there is a pattern in the problem

Basic check

Check the "Spam" folder
Make sure the entered email address is correct
Check the delivery delay (wait 5–10 minutes)

Check via browser tools

Open DevTools (tab Network)
Find the registration request
Check the response status (for example, 200, 400, 500)
Analyze the response body (whether it contains information about sending an email)

Check logs. Contact the development team with a request to check the server logs for errors when sending email. Also check whether requests reach the email service

Stability check

Conduct a series of registrations (10–20 attempts)
Determine the ratio of successful and unsuccessful sendings
Check the dependence on load or time

Analysis of results

Determine whether the problem is permanent or situational
Determine the dependence on:
email provider
execution time
number of simultaneous requests

Determining the cause
Based on the data received, establish a possible cause, for example:

unstable operation of the email service
lack of a resend mechanism
asynchronous processing without result control
lack of error handling (the system shows success even if the sending fails)

9. Recommendations for improvement

Technical:

Add a retry mechanism
Implement error logging
Ensure correct processing of email sending status
Synchronize user messages with sending status

Functional:

Add the ability to resend an email
Add instructions for the user (check the "Spam" folder)

Operational:

Implement email service monitoring
Configure alerts when errors occur

10. Check after correction

Repeat all test scenarios
Check the stability of email sending
Check the operation of the resend mechanism
Check the availability of logging and correct error handling
